# Don't break feature flags

Whenever there are variables with all caps that seem to be used in the same way as the Feature Flags (as in our Rspack Plugin), and they are defined as such in `featureFlags.ts` and `createFeatureFlags.ts`, they are probably feature flags

## Examples

Whenever you see something like

```ts
// biome-ignore lint/style/useSingleVarDeclarator: <explanation>
let DEBUG: boolean
```

Assume it is a Feature Flag and don't change it to something like using `process.env.NODE_ENV` instead